The defect lifecycle represents the journey of a software bug from the moment itâ€™s discovered to when itâ€™s resolved and closed. The stages typically include:

    New â€“ A tester finds a defect and logs it.

    Assigned â€“ The defect is assigned to a developer for fixing.

    Open â€“ The developer starts analyzing and fixing the defect.

    Fixed â€“ The defect has been resolved by the developer.

